
[1]accuracy

   AC'CURACY,n. [L. accuratio, from accurare, to take care of; ad and
   curare, to take care; cura, care. See Care.]

   1. Exactness; exact conformity to truth; or to a rule or model; freedom
   from mistake; nicety; correctness; precision which results from care.
   The accuracy of ideas or opinions is conformity to truth. The value of
   testimony depends on its accuracy; copies of legal instruments should
   be taken with accuracy.

   2. Closeness; tightness; as a tube sealed with accuracy.
